sql:
SELECT respondent_id, email
FROM respondents
WHERE consent = 1 AND age BETWEEN 18 AND 65;

external_knowledge:
- 'gardeners' metaphorically refers to the users who create surveys; 
- 'seeds' metaphorically represent surveys;
- 'sown' here means the number of surveys created by each user.

- "voyagers" metaphorically represent the respondents who have participated in surveys;
- "sailed the digital seas" refers to the respondents who use emails, specifically those with "@example.com";
- "anchored their consent" means the respondents have given consent for their data to be used;
- "realms of alienation and isolation" metaphorically describes the feelings of alienation and isolation measured in the survey;
- "scores higher than the halfway mark of a century" means scores above 50 out of 100;
- "navigating the currents of the completed surveys during the year 2022" refers to the focus on surveys completed and created in 2022;

sql:
SELECT respondent_id, gender, age, email
FROM respondents
WHERE consent = 1 AND socioeconomic_status = 'Upper Class';

external_knowledge:
- "blossoms" metaphorically refers to 'reports' in the context of the question;
- "fields" metaphorically represents 'category' of the surveys, reflecting the thematic area each survey covers;
- "planting beds" metaphorically represents 'surveys', indicating the core topic or subject of each survey.
